You already have the HTML structure for a portfolio. Now let‚Äôs add CSS styling to make it look professional.

Here‚Äôs a sample CSS you can put in a file called style.css and link it in your HTML.

/* Reset some default styles */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Body styling */
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
  background-color: #1e1e2f;
  color: white;
  transition: background-color 1s ease; /* smooth transition for background */
}

/* Header */
header {
  text-align: center;
  background: #2a2a40;
  padding: 2rem;
}

header h1 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

nav a {
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  margin: 0 15px;
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  transition: color 0.3s ease;
}

nav a:hover {
  color: #ff9800;
}

/* Sections */
section {
  padding: 2rem;
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: auto;
}

section h2 {
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  color: #ff9800;
}

/* Project cards */
article {
  background: #33334d;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 10px;
  transition: transform 0.3s ease, background-color 0.3s ease;
}

article:hover {
  transform: translateY(-10px);
  background-color: #444466;
}

/* Footer */
footer {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 1rem;
  background: #2a2a40;
  margin-top: 2rem;
}

üëâ To link this CSS file, add this line inside your HTML <head> section:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">


---

‚ú® Now your portfolio will have:

A dark background with smooth transitions.

A highlight color (#ff9800) for headings and hover effects.

Cards with hover animation for projects.


